description:
Wire the installation gating into the plugin's config hook in src/index.ts.

## Approach: Config hook only (simplified after spike oc-1wef.12)

The spike confirmed that the config hook can both register new commands AND override filesystem commands. This means we only need one mechanism:

```typescript
// In config hook:
const projectContext = await projectContextPromise;
if (projectContext && !projectContext.installReady) {
  input.command = input.command ?? {};
  input.command['init'] = {
    template: getInstallGuideTemplate(),
    description: 'Initialize project for opencode-coder plugin',
  };
}
// When installReady: don't touch input.command.init — let filesystem version run
```

## Changes
- Extend config hook in src/index.ts to conditionally override /init command
- Import getInstallGuideTemplate from src/templates/init-install-guide.ts
- Use the projectContextPromise (already available) to get installReady state
- Do NOT use command.execute.before for this — config hook is sufficient

## Edge cases
- coderPackage not installed: filesystem /init doesn't exist, config hook registers it → works
- coderPackage installed but bd missing: filesystem /init exists, config hook overrides it → works
- everything ready: config hook skips /init → filesystem init.md runs → works
- projectContext is null (detection failed): treat as !installReady → show guidance (safe default)

