description:
## What

Add a `config` hook to the plugin that detects `.coder/AGENTS.md` and adds it to OpenCode's `instructions` array.

## Why

In stealth mode, AGENTS.md lives at `.coder/AGENTS.md` instead of the project root. OpenCode only auto-loads AGENTS.md from the project root. The plugin must bridge this gap by telling OpenCode to also load our file.

## How

In `src/index.ts`, add a `config` hook to the returned `Hooks` object:

```typescript
config: async (input) => {
  const coderAgentsMd = path.join(directory, '.coder', 'AGENTS.md');
  try {
    await fs.access(coderAgentsMd);
    input.instructions = input.instructions || [];
    input.instructions.push('.coder/AGENTS.md');
    logger.info('Injecting .coder/AGENTS.md as additional instructions');
  } catch {
    // .coder/AGENTS.md doesn't exist, nothing to inject
  }
}
```

Key details:
- Use `PluginInput.directory` (or `worktree`) for the base path — the SDK provides this
- The `instructions` array takes relative paths — OpenCode resolves them from project root
- The `config` hook receives the full Config object and can mutate it (documented in SDK)
- This fires once at startup, not per-message — no performance concern
- If the file doesn't exist (team mode), the hook is a no-op

## Acceptance

- `config` hook added to the Hooks object in `src/index.ts`
- When `.coder/AGENTS.md` exists, it appears in the instructions array
- When `.coder/AGENTS.md` does not exist, nothing changes
- Existing hooks (tool.coder, command.execute.before) are not affected
- Tests pass, build succeeds
